<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920120-0076</DOCNO><DOCID>920120-0076.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Sansui Electric Co.:   Pretax Loss of $82.8 Million   Is Expected for 1991 Period</HL><DATE>01/20/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5</SO><CO>   J.SNE U.POL</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)FOOD PRODUCTS (FOD)</IN><NS>EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)FAR EAST (FE)HONG KONG (HK)JAPAN (JA)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Sansui Electric Co., Tokyo, said it expects to post a 1991pretax loss of 10.6 billion yen ($82.8 million) instead ofthe loss of six billion yen predicted in September.   Sales for the year are expected to come in at 20.5 billionyen, below the earlier projection of 26 billion yen, whilethe net loss is expected to total 36 billion yen, larger thanthe loss of 19 billion yen forecast in September.</LP><TEXT>   A company spokesman blamed the grim outlook on aworld-wide slump in audio-visual equipment sales, but addedthat Sansui is being helped by Hong Kong's Grande Group,which owns 31% of Sansui. The stake was transferred to Grandefrom bankrupt Polly Peck International PLC of Britain, whichstill holds 41% of Sansui.   Sansui expects to have a pretax loss of 3.5 billion yen in1992, but a net profit of 500 million yen. Sales are expectedto reach 24 billion yen for the year.</TEXT></DOC>